Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20things%20change%20as%20generations%20change%2C%20including%20fashion%20choices%2C%20eating%20habits%2C%20dating%20styles%2C%20mediums%20of%20communication%20and%20entertainment.%20Certain%20things%20will%20become%20part%20of%20everyday%20life%20as%20things%20change%2C%20while%20others%20are%20forgotten.%20As%20the%20older%20generation%20tries%20to%20adapt%2C%20some%20may%20become%20confused%20by%20this%20at%20times.%20One%20such%20trend%20is%20%26quot%3BBoomer%20Ellipses%26quot%3B%20which%20the%20new%20generation%20is%20trying%20to%20understand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20Gen%20Z%20internet%20users%20have%20reported%20in%20recent%20years%20that%20they%20witness%20older%20individuals%2C%20or%20more%20precisely%20%26quot%3Bboomers%26quot%3B-%20those%20born%20between%201946%20and%201964%2C%20using%20ellipses%20(three%20consecutive%20dots)%20excessively.%20However%2C%20these%20don't%20sit%20well%20with%20the%20Gen%20Z.%20Ellipses%20are%20seen%20by%20younger%20people%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20hesitancy%20or%20passive%20aggression.%20This%20application%20of%20ellipses%20is%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bboomer%20ellipses%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-embed-height%3D%5C%22316%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FNoStupidQuestions%2Fcomments%2Fvzu2iz%2Fwhy_do_boomers_use_ellipses_so_much%2F%5C%22%3EWhy%20do%20boomers%20use%20ellipses%20so%20much%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cnby%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fuser%2FBababool%2F%5C%22%3Eu%2FBababool%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FNoStupidQuestions%2F%5C%22%3ENoStupidQuestions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20became%20viral%20after%20a%20Reddit%20post%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20normal%20tech-savvy%20person%20uses%20ellipses%20to%20basically%20say%2C%20'I%20wanna%20say%20more%20but%20I%20won't.'%20But%20boomers%20use%20it%20all%20the%20time.%20Almost%20every%20professional%20email%2C%20slack%2C%20or%20text%20message%20I%20receive%20is%20always%20something%20along%20'Yes...%20that%20works...'%26quot%3B%20Many%20users%20commented%20on%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGenerational%20differences.%20I'm%20sure%20Boomers%20are%20asking%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20don't%20Zoomers%20use%20proper%20capitalization%20or%20punctuation%3F%26quot%3B%20Both%20answers%3A%20Stylistic%20choices%20that%20reflect%20their%20respective%20generations%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20user.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20take%20%26quot%3BYes...that%20works...%26quot%3B%20as%20meaning%20they%20have%20some%20nitpick%20they%20would%20like%20to%20bring%20up%20but%20it's%20not%20worth%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20GenX%20I%20use%20elipses%2C%20but%20only%20where%20there's%20an%20unsaid%20implication.%20Sort%20of%20like%20'You%20said%20you'd%20think%20about%20the%20answer%20and%20get%20back%20to%20me%20in%205%20minutes.%20It%20has%20been%2010%2C%20so...'%20Somethng%20like%20'Thanks...'%20implies%20to%20me%20they're%20not%20sure%20about%20saying%20thank%20you%2C%20or%20there's%20more%20to%20come.%20Leaving%20that%20hanging%20is%20just%20idiotic%2C%26quot%3B%20remarked%20a%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20user%20commented%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20same%20reason%20young%20people%20end%20phrases%20with%20lol%20and%20lmao%20even%20when%20they%20aren't%20saying%20anything%20funny.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20a%20boomer%20but%20I%20used%20them%20frequently.%20It%20provides%20visual%20context%20in%20order%20to%20get%20a%20point%20across%20better%20by%20adding%20a%20pause%2C%20a%20brief%20moment%20of%20respite%3B%20or%20to%20add%20a%20hint%20of%20inflection%20to%20my%20text.%20These%20are%20used%20pretty%20often%20in%20writting%20and%20in%20books%20so%20it's%20not%20too%20far%20fetched%20to%20use%20them%20in%20every%20day%20writing%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20a%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdam%20Aleksic%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Blinguistics%20influencer%26quot%3B%20on%20Instagram%20recently%20attempted%20to%20theorise%20why%20Gen%20Z%20doesn't%20use%20ellipses%20but%20boomers%20do.%20Ellipses%20technically%20imply%20a%20pause%20that%20something%20has%20been%20purposefully%20omitted%20according%20to%20punctuation%20rules.%20However%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20text-based%20electronic%20communication%2C%20its%20use%20frequently%20varies.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20because%20they%20(boomers)%20grew%20up%20following%20different%20rules%20for%20informal%20communication.%20Nowadays%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20separate%20an%20idea%2C%20you%20just%20press%20enter%20and%20start%20a%20new%20line%20with%20a%20new%20thought.%20But%20it%20made%20less%20sense%20for%20writing%20postcards%20or%20letters%20where%20you%20had%20to%20save%20space.%20So%20people%20back%20in%20the%20day%20learnt%20to%20separate%20thoughts%20by%20using%20ellipses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC8XE3GegQSw%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC8XE3GegQSw%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC8XE3GegQSw%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%